About Us


Founded in 1998, BroadSoft is a leading technology innovator in cloud PBX, unified communications, team collaboration and contact center solutions, designed for our service provider customers across the globe.      


 






























Company
Corporate Info
About Us























Our Culture

We are a multi-national company, multi-cultural and multi-lingual. 
We speak English, French, German, Japanese, Spanish, Portuguese, Dutch, Mandarin, Arabic, Hebrew, Persian, Turkish, Greek, Flemish, Hindi, Romanian, Bulgarian, Finnish, Italian, Russian, Polish, Japanese, Czech, and many others with all their beautiful dialects and flavors. 
We are natives, we are immigrants. Our diversity is our strength. And our corporate culture is grounded on common values as responsible global citizens.
Our passion is to innovate; to enable the human touch via communications and collaboration; empowering people, teams, and companies to remove borders, barriers, walls and silos. 
We are one family. BroadSoft. 






















Our Missionand Vision


 
As a trusted cloud innovator and market leader, we have continuously innovated in cloud unified communication software and services for the last 17 years — and we can’t stop.
Committed to redefining the future of work by inspiring teams to create, collaborate and perform in ways never before imagined, our mission is to bring best-in-class productivity and collaboration tools to businesses.
BroadSoft Business provides a comprehensive, mobile-integrated and completely open communication suite for businesses, with carrier-class reliability and security. By using our technology inspired by users and teams, you can collaborate and communicate more effectively to make your work — simple.

























Our Market Leadership
With 41% market share, we are the industry leader for cloud unified communications with a secure and trusted platform chosen by 25 of the world’s top 30 service providers across 80 countries.














































Our Proven Portfolio
The strength of our innovative technology and robust award-winning portfolio has been recognized by industry pundits from all across the Unified Communications ecosystem.
















BroadSoft’s 41% share of the global hosted IP telephony and UCC services market confirms their leadership position.
Elka Popova, Industry Director, Unified Communications and Collaboration Frost & Sullivan





BroadSoft presently has a clear edge over Microsoft when it comes to cloud voice capabilities, third-party integration, mobility, and contact center capabilities. When considering voice capability, it is clear that BroadSoft’s long history of providing carrier-grade voice functionality provides a service that is far more robust than Microsoft’s Cloud PBX with PSTN connectivity.
E. Brent Kelly, President/Principal Analyst Kelcor Inc.





It gives me great pleasure to honor BroadSoft as a 2016 recipient of TMC’s Unified Communications Product of the Year Award for their innovative product, BroadCloud UC-One. Our judges were very impressed with the ingenuity and excellence displayed by BroadSoft in their groundbreaking work on BroadCloud UC-One.
Rich Tehrani, CEO, TMC





BroadSoft Team-One continues to demonstrate product excellence with its comprehensive solution, updated with integrations with different best-in-class business apps, popular cloud-based file storage services, and a powerful real-time video/audio/messaging function.
2015 Excellence in Technology Award winner - BroadSoft Team-One (formerly Intellinote) Frost & Sullivan





BroadSoft CC-One has a strong ability to analyze and leverage structured and unstructured enterprise data to support business-intelligence-driven contact routing decisions in real time. A simple example is its ability to prioritize calls from customers who previously abandoned a call while waiting in queues.
2015 Magic Quadrant “Visionary” placement for CCaaS, North America - Broadsoft CC-One (formerly Transera) Gartner





The BroadSoft UCaaS consolidation play, as practiced by Vonage, is beneficial to the industry as it builds brand awareness and scaling.
Market Trends: Five Key Trends in the Shifting UCaaS Delivery Landscape, October 2015 Gartner 




































Our Subsidiaries










Placetel is a leading cloud PBX provider and a wholly-owned subsidiary of BroadSoft. Based out of Cologne, Germany, Placetel’s award-winning telephone system is primarily aimed at small and midsize businesses and contains more than 100 powerful features that can be managed flexibly. More than 12,000 customers have already opted for a cloud PBX solution from Placetel.













BroadSoft Japan KK is a pioneer in creating innovative cloud-based communication solutions in Japan and a wholly-owned subsidiary of BroadSoft. Based out of Tokyo, Japan, it provides hosted UC services that service providers deliver to the Japanese market of 5 million small businesses — over 70% of Japan’s work force.






















