BroadSoft - Wikipedia





















 






BroadSoft

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search






This article contains content that is written like an advertisement. Please help improve it by removing promotional content and inappropriate external links, and by adding encyclopedic content written from a neutral point of view. (December 2014) (Learn how and when to remove this template message)



BroadSoft Inc.





Type

Public


Traded as
NASDAQ: BSFT


Industry
Communication software


Founded
1998; 19 years ago (1998)


Headquarters
Gaithersburg, Maryland, United States


Revenue
$278 Million(As of 2015[update])[1]


Website
http://www.broadsoft.com/


BroadSoft, Inc. (NASDAQ: BSFT) is a global communication software and service provider with over 500 customers worldwide supporting millions of subscribers.[1][2][3][4] The company provides cloud-based Unified Communications solutions to communications service providers, based on their UC-One solution which consists of two product platforms, BroadWorks and BroadCloud. [5] In 2013 the company acquired the British company Hosted IP Communications (Europe) Ltd. (HIPCOM)[6] and the German company Finocom AG, both providers of cloud-delivered unified communications services.[3]



Contents


1 Background
2 Awards
3 References
4 External links



Background[edit]
The company was founded by Michael Tessler and Scott D. Hoffpauir in 1998.[7] The products and services of the company play a critical part in the network by serving as the software which delivers and coordinates call control and information transmission over service providers’ IP-based network.[8] Its products include BroadWorks and BroadCloud. The company’s flagship product, BroadWorks, is a Voice over Internet Protocol (VoIP) applications platform that enables service providers to deliver basic and enhanced voice services for business and residential end users. - See more at: http://www.broadsoft.com/service-providers/products-applications/broadworks/#sthash.BkrN9LWt.dpuf. BroadCloud is a fully managed service that delivers BroadSoft’s comprehensive Unified Communications services. - See more at: http://www.broadsoft.com/service-providers/products-applications/broadcloud/#sthash.8QiU844g.dpuf In 2014, the company was selected as the supplier of Sprint Corporation (NASDAQ: S) for its next generation multimedia system-based network and VoLTE development.[9]
On May 31, 2016 BroadSoft, Inc. announced the acquisition of Reston, Virginia-based Intellinote, an enterprise messaging-based team communication and collaboration software application built for the increasingly mobile and millennial workforce.[10]
Awards[edit]
In 2013, the company received Frost & Sullivan 2013 New Product Innovation Leadership Award for its hosted unified communication platform product.[11] In the same year, thanks to its unified communication platform, UC-one, it won the People's Choice Stevie Award in the 11th American Business Award Competition. UC-one was listed in "Favorite Telecommunications Service" list.[12]
